ude of tranquility that delineates the service quarters at the front of the property from the private and social realms in the back. Designed as single-story rectilinear volumes, both the service and living quarters are punctuated by oval-shaped patios, their organic contours softening the stark architectural geometry.\u003cstrong\u003e Each patio serves its own purpose—to greet, rest, or entertain—transforming the home into a fluid, multi-layered living environment.\u003c/strong\u003e In conjunction with floor-to-ceiling glazing, they also dissolve the boundary between interior and exterior, allowing light and air to animate the spaces with a quiet dynamism.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/26_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/26_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"2560\" alt=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" title=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/26_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/28_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/28_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1919\" alt=