 \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/30_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/30_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"2789\" alt=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" title=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/30_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/33_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/33_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"2908\" alt=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" title=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/33_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/34_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/34_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"2874\" alt=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" title=\"Photography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/34_white_fortress_kuwait_taep_aap_fernando_guerra_fg_sg_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Fernando Guerra | FG+SG.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eEmbracing its coastal position, the plot terminates in an open, semi-covered terrace overlooking the sea.\u003cstrong\u003e This space is the home’s ultimate threshold, a liminal zone between the building and the private beach that encapsulates the intimate relationship between the architecture and its natural setting. \u003c/strong\u003eLandscaping also plays a crucial role in this dialogue, with native vegetation interwoven into the building volumes. These natural elements temper the built environment, reinforcing the home’s commitment to a sensorial connection with its surroundings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn its current context, White Fortress is a paradox—a secluded stronghold within \u003cstrong\u003eSabah Al Ahmad Sea City\u003c/strong\u003e, a master-planned city set to accommodate 250,000 residents over the coming decades spread over 200 kilometres of waterfront unfolding across an intricate web of artificial canals. As this new coastal world takes shape, the residence stands as an early marker, a home that looks both at the present and the future, where traditional sensibilities and 